rComments: One of the worst professors at the university, spouts utter nonsense about health and race unsupported by scientific fact, false information that is harmful to minorities, and if you disagree with her opinions you will probably get a bad grade. Confrontational, rude, and aggressive for no reason, overall a bad experience.
Took a seminar course with her called "Black Health in Canada". The class was full of great discussions. Prof gives feedback and good insight on how to do better in assignments.

She developed this course (Black Health in Canada) and you can tell she's extremely passionate about the subject. The seminar style was run super well in my opinion and the readings were excellent. Heavy course especially condensed in 6 weeks. Final project was a group podcast which was super fun, also lots of participation marks.

The online Determinants of Health is not too bad. Since it is online I'm not too sure how much the prof affects the content, but she was very accessible through email and went over the midterm in a 3-hour lecture with good feedback. It is easy to fall behind in an online class so don't let yourself do that.

Her lectures are dry, her midterm is brutal and she talks faster than Charlie Sheen can say winning after taking drugs. The course itself shouldn't even really be a course in the first place. She was also very confrontational, which doesn't really help her, because her future is in the students' hands. Glad to be done with her... hopefully for good

OK prof, but she needs to work on her speed. Would go through 50 slide PPT in 40 minutes. Make sure you do the assigned readings because she will test on it!! Her midterm (only one) questions were VERY LONG. Paragraph MCQ questions with paragraph MCQ answers. Group project was easy. Final paper tough, but if you start early you'll do fine.

Engaging lectures, especially in the second half during the "special topics" section, also brings in guest speakers. High expectations for amount of reading and quality of work. First midterm was very difficult with a low class average, second assignment was a group podcast which was more manageable, final was a paper on policy analysis - hard.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Tough grader']
